Senate Government Operations 1
Amendment No. 1 to SB2257
Jackson
Signature of Sponsor
AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 2257 House Bill No. 1451*
by deleting subsection (b) in SECTION 1 and substituting:
(b) No later than January 1, 2027, unless the governing body of a county has
constituted a fully functioning local ethics board of at least five (5) voting members and
one (1) nonvoting ethics officer, ethics oversight reverts to the state ethics commission
until and unless the state ethics commission determines, by a formal written decision,
that the local ethics board is in full compliance with all state ethics requirements for
counties.
